# Single source of truth for the bene version used by CI gates and swarms.
#
# Why pin: the regression gate, refactor swarm, and review swarm all import
# bene. If they ran against the same `bene/` source tree the PR is editing,
# a self-bug on a PR branch could break the gate that is supposed to catch
# the bug. Pinning isolates the tooling from the change under review.
#
# Pinned to a PUBLISHED PyPI version (not a git SHA) so the pin survives the
# single-commit history consolidation done before each release — a SHA pin
# dangles the moment main is squashed; an immutable PyPI version does not.
#
# Update protocol:
#   1. Publish the new bene release to PyPI (uv build && uv publish).
#   2. Bump BENE_VERSION here.
#   3. CODEOWNERS reviews the bump as a privileged change.
BENE_VERSION=0.2.0
